identified_cves.description: Critical remote code execution vulnerability in Microsoft SMBv1 server that allows unauthenticated attackers to execute arbitrary code
identified_cves.technical_details: EternalBlue exploits a buffer overflow in the SMBv1 protocol implementation. The vulnerability occurs when the server fails to properly handle specially crafted packets, allowing attackers to achieve remote code execution with SYSTEM privileges.
